      .parallax_group#group1
        .parallax_layer.parallax_layer-main
          .content
            :markdown-it(html)
              # The Problem
              Persistent organic pollutants (POPs), including PFOS (perfluorooctanesulfonic acid) and PCBs (polychlorinated biphenyls), have been of great concern in the past decades, due to their toxicity even at low concentrations. Their bioaccumulating properties  lead to alarming concentrations in ecosystems. However, current detection methods for POPs are expensive and time-consuming.
        .parallax_layer.parallax_layer-reef
          img(src=require('./assets/img/Home--reef1.png')['default']).reef
          .reefblock
        .parallax_layer.parallax_layer-fore
          img(src=require('./assets/img/Home--fore1.png')['default']).fore

      .parallax_group#group2
        .parallax_layer.parallax_layer-main
          .content
            :markdown-it(html)
              # Our Project
              S-POP aims to solve this issue by creating a monitor containing two major parts, a modular E. coli biosensor coupled with a Microbial Fuel Cell. Read more about our project [here](https://2020.igem.org/Team:Stockholm/Description).
        .parallax_layer.parallax_layer-reef
          img(src=require('./assets/img/Home--reef2.png')['default']).reef
          .reefblock
        .parallax_layer.parallax_layer-fore
          img(src=require('./assets/img/Home--fore2.png')['default']).fore

      .parallax_group#group3
        .parallax_layer.parallax_layer-main
          .content
            :markdown-it(html)
              # Design
              When E. coli is activated by the pollutant, a Quorum sensing (QS) molecule is produced. Upregulated by the QS-molecule, engineered Shewanella oneidensis produces an oscillating electrical signal whose pattern corresponds to the type of pollutants in the sample. Read more about our project design here [here](https://2020.igem.org/Team:Stockholm/Design).
        .parallax_layer.parallax_layer-reef
          img(src=require('./assets/img/Home--reef3.png')['default']).reef
          .reefblock
        .parallax_layer.parallax_layer-fore
          img(src=require('./assets/img/Home--fore3.png')['default']).fore

